			<DIV>
<P class=MsoNormal **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0in justify; TEXT-ALIGN: 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto?><FONT size=2>1. Please fix our broken and/or overpriced AA's </FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0in justify; TEXT-ALIGN: 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto?><FONT size=2>Turn Undead  a level 59 class specific AA that does not work on level 55+ mobs. Suggestions: Remove the fear, fix the cast time to not scale up with level of the AA. The excessive cast time at level 3 makes it less useful than at level 1. Or... completely alter what it is (like what was done to CR) and turn it into a focus effect for undead nukes/dots, or something similar (like a melee undead focus/bane). <FONT color=#66ff00>(Part of the proposed first pass with class re-envisioning posted on EQLive on 3/14/2005)</FONT></FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0in justify; TEXT-ALIGN: 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto?><FONT size=2>2. Move short duration buffs to the song window, i.e. Yaulp, HOTs, Mind Wrack&nbsp;&nbsp; <FONT color=#ff0000>(No change planned at this time)</FONT></FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0in justify; TEXT-ALIGN: 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto?><FONT size=2>Between Rangers spamming their attack buffs and SK/necros using their recourse taps, "buff management" means clicking off 5 crap buffs every other minute. <BR>&nbsp;<BR>This still an issue due to the abundance of hybrid buffs added to the game post 50. New suggestions: either lower the Omens AA to a level 51 buy in, or add some buff slots for lower level characters. <BR>&nbsp;<BR>3. Please reevaluate a clerics non-healing skills and abilities. <FONT color=#ff0000>(Currently being discussed)</FONT> - Most likely this will be considered as part of the class re-envisioning</FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0in justify; TEXT-ALIGN: 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto?><FONT size=2>Most classes offer more than a single role to a group, or even if limited to DPS only, can fill several group slots and stack. Clerics lack this flexibility, due to the lack of healing being able to stack. (there is no value to over healing) <BR>&nbsp;<BR>a. Please give clerics some capability to solo efficiently. <BR>Introduce lower version of our wards in the game (they are on Lucy but not in game yet). Clerics also need a way to stop runners, since we can't seriously damage them. Suggestions include a strong but short root, lower the chance our procs have to break root, or a spell to make mobs not wanting to run.<BR>b. Cleric melee was an addition to replace lost value in being the sole healer for a great deal of content. <BR>Please make sure this ability scales as well as the role we lost. While the proc is a unique concept, it is static. Either itemization needs to be much better, or code written to replace the summoned hammers with a castable proc that will work with any weapon/item and scale with levels. The second part of this is the base melee skill has never been reviewed since the original game release. There is no valid reason for non-melee classes to continue to be punished with non-existent melee skills. <BR>c. Cleric offensive spells have not kept up vs. other casters through the levels.<BR>While we expect specialist classes (wizards, mages) to be the clear best, no class should face stagnation to the point of valuelessness. <BR><EM>Level 49 Clr: 42.64dps, 2.15dpm, level 69 Clr: 112.07dps, 3.32dpm <BR>Level 49 Dru: 71.63dps, 2.45dpm, level 69 Dru: 220.11dps, 4.35dpm <BR>Level 49 Shm: 71.88dps, 2.00dpm, Level 69 Shm: 123.50dps, 3.39dpm <BR></EM>d. Our specialist spells have similarly suffered; at 49 we were equal to wizards using our undead nukes, now we fall far short, both in DPS and efficiency.<BR>Suggestions include review of DPM ratios, and consider converting anti-undead spells to an Alteration skill base. (for specialization value). <BR>Our undead DoTs were originally added via expansions. Many clerics question the reason for this since they are not as efficient as out DD spells of similar levels, however ALL other classes with both DoT and DD spells show a clear pattern of the DoTs exceeding the DD effciantcy, even for DDs of higher spell levels. Why arent cleric DoTs similer in this regard? Also, why is our DoT spell range reduced? Suggestions for improvement include normalizing the above, and/or consideration of changing the basic nature of undead spells to be more of an anti evil, including both undead and demonic/summoned/corrupted model types (and removing the anti summoned spells of clerics and other classes and replacing them with this new single spell set as well) <BR>e. Please give clerics some clear ability to perform a non-healing group role. <BR>Clerics in a group setting that does not require healing are a clear hindrance if another healing class of similar level and equipment is available. The above changes would affect this greatly, or some other idea, such as a CC related role, or new spells/abilities to assist the group as a whole (chant style spells similar to bardic magic, that would require the cleric to focus on one task, but aid the group)<BR>f. Cleric (as well as all caster) skills have not risen at all since Kunark until OoW. (with the exception of adding bash to the class). <BR>Please re-evaluate the use of skills for clerics, and the relative value of skills compared to other classes. (why does a cleric with the same skills hit less often and for less damage than a melee class?) <BR>&nbsp;<BR>4. Please evaluate the defensive skills and abilities of clerics. <FONT color=#ff0000>(Currently being discussed)</FONT>&nbsp; - Most likely this will be considered as part of the class re-envisioning</FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0in justify; TEXT-ALIGN: 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto?><FONT size=2>Due to data that we as players cannot see, a similarly equipped cleric/knight will have varying results on actual damage taken (not hit rate, which is controlled by secondary skills, but actual damage per hit) It is our belief that clerics have enough real penalties due to lack of secondary skills (repost, parry, aa), that also having softcaps and tables that lead to different results with the same skills is excessive and detrimental. <BR>&nbsp;<BR>5. Please add group versions of our buffs at all levels. <FONT color=#ff0000>(Currently being discussed)</FONT></FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0in justify; TEXT-ALIGN: 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto?><FONT size=2>This was something done for druids, but never for other classes. our AC buffs are generally seen as weak except late game so not used, one other possibility is to combine the ac into the symbol (hp type 2) line, now that they do not have a gem cost (this would also make room for group type 1 spells or group symbol spells at all levels)<BR>&nbsp;<BR>6. Make AotZ Stack with Focus. The paladin self buff is quite similar to the cleric self buff. As the paladin buff stacks with focus it seems reasonable that the cleric buff should likewise stack with focus <FONT color=#ff0000>(currently being evaluated)</FONT> </FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0in justify; TEXT-ALIGN: 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto?><FONT size=2>If clerics are asked to perform a more melee centric role to solo/add to a group, then this extra survivability will benefit us as well as it does both paladins and Shadow knights in current content. Both classes self buff now stack with the Focus line. The DS component is considered generally wish list, and a possible solution to solo balance, as such it is not appropriate for this item and was removed. <BR>&nbsp;<BR>7. Improve stun line  increase level caps&nbsp; <FONT color=#ff0000>(currently being evaluated)</FONT> </FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0in justify; TEXT-ALIGN: 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto?><FONT size=2>The main problem here being that lower level stuns in the 50s do not work post 55 (as paladin stuns do), also the secondary effects (DD + pushback) make using these spells undesirable in much content. Finally, the excessive recast delays (that other classes with stuns do not have as severely as clerics) and unexplained timer setup on OoW stuns again reduce the use of these spells. <BR>&nbsp;<BR>8. Please re-evaluate cleric options for normal invisibility.&nbsp; <FONT color=#66ff00>(Part of the proposed first pass with class re-envisioning posted on EQLive on 3/14/2005)</FONT> - improved invis potions</FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0in justify; TEXT-ALIGN: 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto?><FONT size=2>Suggestions include: A self only invis spell, a self only improved invis spell; Improved invis potions, stackable invis potions, soulbound invis items, more unlimited clickie invis items, finally a minimum duration for cloudy potions (2 minutes). </FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0in justify; TEXT-ALIGN: 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto?><FONT size=2>The goal is to find some tool or way to assist clerics with both travel, and specifically CR. Clerics are perhaps in the worst possible situation in that we are needed to CR most groups, but completely lack utility to do so. Sanctuary was a possibility, but it doesnt stop mobs from attacking you. Even though it is desirable to have clerics work with others to mitigate this problem, it too often simply falls on the cleric to figure it out without assistance. This is a major downtime/deadtime penalty that clerics face (and is more frustrating than difficult, so simply detracts from the game)<BR>&nbsp;<BR>9. Combine the Symbol and AC lines of buffs<FONT color=#ff0000> (No change planned at this time)</FONT></FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0in justify; TEXT-ALIGN: 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto?><FONT size=2>This would kill several birds with one stone: there is no group version of our AC buff line, it would free a buff slot, and it would reduce the annoyance of casting many spells, when Conviction is not the buff of choice.<BR>&nbsp;<BR>10. Please increase the range of our group heals <FONT color=#0033ff><STRONG>(NEW)</STRONG></FONT></FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0in justify; TEXT-ALIGN: 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto?><FONT size=2>There is an inconsistency between range of our Divine Arbitration abilities (AA and on epic) and the range of group heals that are used after arbitrating to heal the group. Also, the short range is really annoying, in particular with recent encounters that involve huge models and AoE rampage. Finally, it would be a step toward reducing the number of healers required in raid.</FONT></P></DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							Kytherea ~~wielding a giant hammer & a hairless War Hamster~~<br><br>"I'm late, I'm late...."
							</div>
								
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
